ZCZC GE44
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 182300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE LIES 997 W OF ROCKALL
WITH A WEAK RIDGE ACROSS IBERIA. TOWARDS SCANDINAVIA AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE
LIES 1027 ON THE NORWAY COAST WITH A RIDGE EXTENDING ACROSS CULLERCOATS.
OVERNIGHT THE ATLANTIC LOW FILLS AND SINKS SWARDS TO LIE 1003 OVER SHANNON
BY DAWN WHILST THE SCANDINAVIAN HIGH DRIFTS INTO THE NORWEGIAN SEA. THERE
IS LITTLE CHANGE TO THE SYNOPTIC PATTERN THROUGH THURSDAY BUT DURING FRIDAY
THE ATLANTIC LOW DEEPENS AGAIN TO LIE 994 OVER FITZROY BY MIDDAY AND THE
NORWEGIAN HIGH BUILDS TO 1038. THIS PATTERN PERSISTS ACROSS UK SEA WATERS
UNTIL THE END OF THE PERIOD. HAZARDOUS WINDS NOT EXP NEAR THE START OF THE
PERIOD. STRG WINDS SPREADING ACROSS DOGGER GERMAN BIGHT HUMBER AND THAMES
ON FRIDAY AND SATURDAY. STRG WINDS ALSO POSS ACROSS NERN PARTS OF VIKING
AND FAIR ISLE ON FRIDAY
